<!-- §6 FACTORS (enriched · R-08) -->
<section class="dsec" id="factors"><div class="wrap">
  <div class="sec-head"><div><div class="eyebrow">{T.factors.eye} · {T.factors.q}</div><h2>{T.factors.h}.</h2></div><span class="fresh-tag">{T.factors.fresh}</span></div>
  <p class="lead" set:html={T.factors.lead}></p>
  <div class="snap">
    <div class="kpibar">{T.factors.kpi.map((k) => (<div class="kpi"><div class="kpi-k" set:html={k[0]}></div><div class={`kpi-v${k[1] === '—' ? ' pend' : ''}`}>{k[1]}</div><div class="kpi-meta"><span class="vt">{k[2]}</span>{k[3] && (<span class={`dconf ${k[3]}`}>{k[3]}</span>)}</div></div>))}</div>
  </div>
  <div class="track-grid">
    <div class="track"><div class="tk-h">What we track</div><ul>{T.factors.track.map(([x, m]) => (<li><span class={`mn mn-${m}`}>{m}</span><span set:html={x}></span></li>))}</ul></div>
    <div class="track-side"><div class="lvbox"><div class="lv-h">Leading-indicator value</div><div class="lv-v">{T.factors.lv[0]}</div><p>{T.factors.lv[1]}</p></div><div class="srcline"><b>Sources</b> <span class="dconf tierchip">{T.factors.tier}</span> {T.factors.src}</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="deep">
    <div class="dcallout mt20a"><div class="dc-h">DTS is the risk unit — and DTS is destiny</div><p>Spread volatility scales with the spread <b>level</b>, not duration alone, so the risk unit of credit is <b>DTS = duration × spread</b> (the post-2007 industry standard, Ben Dor–Dynkin). A 1y bond at 500 bp and a 5y bond at 100 bp carry the <i>same</i> DTS of 500. The corollary the desk lives by: if spreads widen 50%, a book's DTS rises ~50% <b>with no trades placed</b> — you become mechanically <i>longer</i> risk in a sell-off, exactly when you'd want less.</p></div>
    <div class="dcallout mt14t"><div class="dc-h">Carry is not clean alpha</div><p>A "diversified multi-factor" sleeve is often <b>one trade</b>: carry, value and reach-for-yield all load on the same systematic spread beta. Robeco's own researchers find carry's risk-adjusted edge over the market is <i>statistically insignificant</i> and a carry book "behaves very similarly to a value portfolio." The genuine diversifiers are <b>momentum</b> (which can go short high-beta names) and <b>up-in-quality / low-risk</b> — the only factor reliably <i>short</i> DTS.</p></div>
    <div class="tk-h mt22a">Factor rotation by volatility regime — information ratio</div>
    <div class="tblwrap"><table class="dtbl"><thead><tr><th>Factor</th><th>Low-VIX (calm)</th><th>High-VIX (stress)</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>{factorVix.map((r) => (<tr><td class="nm">{r[0]}</td><td class={`sens ${fvTone(r[1])}`}>{r[1]}</td><td class={`sens ${fvTone(r[2])}`}>{r[2]}</td></tr>))}</tbody></table></div>
    <div class="tk-h mt18a">IG factor return by regime — % per month</div>
    <div class="tblwrap"><table class="dtbl"><thead><tr><th>Factor</th><th>Expansion</th><th>Contraction</th><th>Downturn</th><th>Repair</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>{factorRegime.map((r) => (<tr><td class="nm">{r[0]}</td><td class={`sens ${fvTone(r[1])}`}>{r[1]}</td><td class={`sens ${fvTone(r[2])}`}>{r[2]}</td><td class={`sens ${fvTone(r[3])}`}>{r[3]}</td><td class={`sens ${fvTone(r[4])}`}>{r[4]}</td></tr>))}</tbody></table></div>
    <div class="tk-h mt22a">How credit factors behaved in stress</div>
    <div class="tblwrap"><table class="dtbl"><thead><tr><th>Episode</th><th>What led / what broke</th><th>Sourced magnitude</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>{factorCrisis.map((r) => (<tr><td class="nm" set:html={r[0]}></td><td set:html={r[1]}></td><td class="num-cell">{r[2]}</td></tr>))}</tbody></table></div>
    <p class="tnote">Information ratios: Invesco, Jan 2001–Jul 2023. Regime returns: Northern Trust, Jan 2004–Dec 2023. "Carry ≈ value": Robeco (Houweling et&nbsp;al. 2017). DTS: Ben Dor–Dynkin (2007). Crisis magnitudes: MSCI, Angelo Gordon, Guggenheim, Eco3min/FRED. Northern Trust regimes: expansion/contraction are economic, downturn/repair credit. Sourced historical readings, not forecasts; IR = information ratio.</p>
